&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chief Technology Officer (CTO)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Toronto, Ontario (Hybrid) or Montréal, Québec (Hybrid)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to: CEO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Level: Executive / C-Suite&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trolley is the payouts platform for the internet economy. Our mission is to unlock the global economic opportunity of the internet by building a truly borderless payouts ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through our platform and API, Trolley enables businesses to pay people anywhere in the world, supporting creators, on demand workers, and suppliers at scale. Companies rely on Trolley as mission-critical infrastructure to automate payouts, collect tax and banking information, and reduce fraud and risk, all in one place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, Trolley is the trusted payouts solution for hundreds of businesses, including Canva, Soundcloud, and Envato. We’ve processed millions of payments globally, helping creators, artists, and suppliers get paid quickly, securely, and with confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Trolley enters its next stage of growth, we will be heavily investing in AI to accelerate product innovation, improve operational efficiency, and transform how software is built across the company. We are seeking a Chief Technology Officer (CTO) to lead our technology organization and help define how AI shapes the future of Trolley.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CTO will be a key member of Trolley&#39;s executive leadership team, responsible for defining and executing the company&#39;s technology strategy while ensuring the scalability, security, reliability, and innovation of our platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A critical mandate for the successful candidate will be driving AI adoption across the engineering team and broader company. We are looking for a leader who has successfully implemented AI powered development practices, enabled organization wide adoption, and delivered measurable improvements in engineering productivity, software quality, and speed of execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CTO will oversee Engineering and Information Security while partnering closely with Product, Operations, Finance, Compliance, and GTM leaders to align technology investments with company objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Define and Execute Trolley&#39;s Technology Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute Trolley&#39;s long term technology vision and roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the CEO and executive leadership team to align technology investments with company strategy and growth objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the platform remains scalable, secure, reliable, and capable of supporting Trolley&#39;s continued global expansion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate emerging technologies and identify opportunities to create competitive advantage and improve operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead architectural decisions that support long term product innovation and business growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead AI Transformation Across the Organization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute Trolley&#39;s AI strategy across Engineering and the broader organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive adoption of AI powered software development practices, coding assistants, testing automation, QA automation, observability, and operational tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish measurable improvements in engineering productivity, software quality, and delivery velocity through AI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to leverage AI within products, customer experiences, internal operations, and decision making

